The paper presents a deep learning model, specifically an autoencoder, to analyze gene expression profiles and distinguish between normal and cancer cells. This involves dimensionality reduction, unsupervised learning, and feature extraction, which are all common topics in machine learning and artificial intelligence. The use of HPC-focused deep learning toolkit also suggests a focus on efficient computation and parallelization, which could fall under computer architecture or high-performance computing. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.CV (Computer Vision). Other possible sub-categories include cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science).
